<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Golan Withdrawal `Principal Demand' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: Golan Withdrawal `Principal Demand' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605193794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1815 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Under the patronage of President Hafiz al-Asad, 
the Artists Association this evening held a central festival on 
the occasion of the First Artists Day in the 8 March Theater in 
Damascus. 
  Sulayman Qaddah, assistant regional secretary of the Arab 
Socialist Ba'th Party, deputized for the president. [passage 
omitted] 
  Comrade Sulayman Qaddah delivered a speech on the occasion 
in 
which he conveyed President Hafiz al-Asad's greetings and 
appreciation to the Syrian artists. [passage omitted] 
  Comrade Qaddah then spoke about Syria's steadfastness and 
adherence to pan-Arab rights and firm principles to establish 
peace. He explained that Syria fought in honor and is 
negotiating in honor, and seeks the just and comprehensive peace 
based on the principles of the international legitimacy, the UN 
resolutions, and the land-for-peace formula. He said: Within 
this context, Syria believes Israel's withdrawal from the Golan 
Heights and return to the pre-5 June 1967 borders is a principal 
demand and a basic thing that cannot be avoided if peace is to 
be established and if security and stability are to prevail in 
the region. 
  He said: Under the historic leadership of its faithful 
leader Hafiz al-Asad, Syria rose with the glorious Corrective 
Movement to build itself, resist aggression, and struggle 
against occupation. It sticks to the pan-Arab facts and the firm 
principles. It depends in its steadfastness on the wisdom and 
courage of its leader and on its sons' efforts, unity, and 
interaction with their country's concerns, as well as their 
enthusiasm to develop and bolster their country's prosperity and 
stability so that Syria will always enjoy the steadfast pan-Arab 
position and the pioneering national role. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

