<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   South Yemen's al-'Attas Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Yemen's al-'Attas Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605203594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 2026 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, former [Yemeni] prime 
minister and envoy of 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of 
the Yemeni Socialist Party, arrived this evening in Damascus. 
He is accompanied by 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Dali, member of the 
[Socialist] Party Political Bureau. 
  He was received at Damascus International Airport by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar'. 
  Mr. al-'Attas made a statement to a Syrian Arab News Agency, 
SANA, correspondent in which he said: I am pleased to visit 
fraternal Syria. I look forward to meeting with President Hafiz 
al-Asad and the brother officials to exchange views on 
conditions in Yemen. 
  He added: We have great confidence in the efforts Syria is 
exerting to end the fighting and preserve Yemen's unity and what 
can be saved of the ties of brotherhood that were hit and 
greatly affected by the war. 

</TEXT>

