<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Zu'bi Receives Egyptian Petroleum Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Zu'bi Receives Egyptian Petroleum Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605190394 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1400 today, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi 
received Egyptian Petroleum Minister Dr. Hamdi al-Banbi. The 
meeting was attended by Dr. Nadir Nabulsi, minister of oil and 
mineral resources; the director general of the Syrian Oil 
Company; and the Egyptian ambassador in Egypt. Discussions 
dealt with the existing relations of oil cooperation between the 
two sisterly countries. 
  Meanwhile, the Syrian-Egyptian oil subcommittee began 
meetings at the Oil Ministry today. The Syrian side was led by 
Dr. Nadir Nabulsi, minister of oil and mineral resources. The 
Egyptian side was led by Petroleum Minister Dr. Hamdi al-Banbi. 
Discussions at the meeting dealt with issues pertaining to 
bilateral oil cooperation and ways of bolstering it for the 
joint benefit of both counties. It was agreed to establish a 
joint Syrian-Egyptian company for drilling and maintaining wells 
and to refer its draft law to competent authorities to complete 
the terms of its establishment and its economic feasibility. 
  The oil minister said this agreement is a true translation 
of 
the instructions of the political leaderships of both Syria and 
Egypt. 
  The meeting was attended by the delegation accompanying the 
Egyptian petroleum minister and the director general of the 
Syrian Oil Company. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

