<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Zu'bi, Qaddah Receive CPC Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Zu'bi, Qaddah Receive CPC Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2505135794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2505135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1200 today, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi 
received a CPC delegation, led by Comrade Wei Jianxing, member 
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and head of 
the Chinese Federation of Trade Unions. The Chinese ambassador 
in Damascus attended the meeting. 
  Comrade Jianxing conveyed greetings from Chinese Premier Li 
Peng to Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi who also asked Jianxing 
to convey his greetings to Mr. Li Peng. 
  The talks dealt with the means of promoting the existing 
relations of cooperation between the two friendly countries. 
  Comrade Dr. Sulayman Qaddah, assistant regional secretary of 
the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party [ASBP], earlier today received 
Comrade Wei Jianxing and the accompanying delegation. The 
Chinese ambassador in Damascus attended the meeting. 
  During the meeting, the two sides reviewed relations of 
friendship and cooperation between the ASBP and the CPC and 
means of promoting them. 
  The ASBP assistant regional secretary briefed the guest 
delegation on the developments of the political situation in the 
region and the peace process. He also explained the obstacles 
placed by Israel to abort the peace process and to divert it 
from the bases, principles, and formulas it was based on. 
  Comrade Qaddah expressed Syria's concern about the 
establishment of a just and comprehensive peace based on the 
principles of international legitimacy, UN resolutions, and the 
land-for-peace formula that guarantees the liberation of the 
entire Golan and withdrawal to the pre-5 June 1967 border. 
  Comrade Jianxing praised Syria's stands under the leadership 
of President Hafiz al-Asad, its desire to achieve a just and 
comprehensive peace, and its central and decisive role in this 
regard. He also reiterated China's support for the 
implementation of UN Security Council Resolutions 242, 338, and 
425, which constitute the basis of the peace process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

