<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Meets Al-Asad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Meets Al-Asad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2605151294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2605151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1000 today in Latakia, His Excellency President 
Hafiz al-Asad received Mr. Wei Jianxing, member of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, 
who is also head of the Chinese Federation of Trade Unions, and 
his delegation. 
  The meeting was attended by comrade 'Abdallah al-Ahmar, 
assistant secretary general of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Barty, 
and Mr. Li Qingyu, the PRC's ambassador in Damascus. Mr. Wei 
conveyed greetings from PRC President Jiang Zemin and Prime 
Minister Li Ping to his excellency the president. Acknowledging 
the greetings, his excellency asked that they communicate his 
greetings and good wishes to the Chinese leadership and people. 
  The Chinese delegation told the president they were 
satisfied 
with their talks in Damascus and that they would help boost ties 
between the two countries. The Chinese delegation said they 
were impressed by the advancment made by Syria, led by his 
excellency the president. The sides discussed the Middle East, 
with the Chinese delegation applauding Syria's position on the 
peace process. They said China's Middle East policies were in 
line with Syria's position as far as the peace process goes. A 
standing invitation for his excellency the presdient to visit 
China was renewed. The president promised to make the visit at 
an appropriate date. 

</TEXT>

