<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister, Finnish Delegation Discuss Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister, Finnish Delegation Discuss Economic Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2705074594 Damascus AL-BA'TH in Arabic 11 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> JN2705074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus AL-BA'TH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus (SANA) -- Dr. Salim Yasin, deputy prime 
minister for economic affairs, has met with the Finnish economic 
and trade delegation currently visiting Syria. The delegation 
includes officials from Finnish Government ministries and 
departments as well as businessmen representing different 
sectors. 
  During this meeting, the conferees reviewed economic and 
trade relations between the two countries and the prospects for 
commercial and economic dealings in the public, private, and 
mixed sectors. The conferees also reviewed the possibility of 
joint ventures between businessmen in both countries and the 
participation of Finnish companies and firms in Syrian projects. 
  Dr. Yasin also replied to questions from members of the 
Finnish delegation on the development of the different sectors 
of the Syrian national economy. 

</TEXT>

