<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqis Arrested for Illegally Entering Kuwait </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqis Arrested for Illegally Entering Kuwait </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705092894 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 2000 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 26 May (KUNA) -- Kuwait security sources 
said today that the Interior Ministry's Coast Guard 
administration has arrested eight Iraqis on Tuesday [24 May] 
afternoon after entering the country from the sea in a wooden 
boat. 
  The sources added that the initial investigations revealed 
that the detainees claimed that they entered the Kuwaiti 
territorial waters for fishing. The sources said that the 
detainees have been referred to the competent bodies. 

</TEXT>

