<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin, Ministers View Palestinian Plans for Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin, Ministers View Palestinian Plans for Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2705050094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 27 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2705050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin last night held 
consultations with a number of cabinet ministers on Palestinian 
plans regarding the establishment of institutions in Jerusalem 
and creating facts on the ground. 
  Qol Yisra'el's political affairs reporter says the ministers 
were told that the Palestinians are seeking, among other 
measures, to establish an economic authority and a university. 
They also want to have Orient House -- the unofficial PLO 
headquarters -- granted special status and they want to deploy 
their own security operatives in the area. 

</TEXT>

