<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Services Kill 23 Members of Armed Groups </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Services Kill 23 Members of Armed Groups </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805231494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805231494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The security services announced today the killing of 
several members of armed groups during the last three days, more 
details with our correspondent: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] In a communique issued today, 
the security services said that 23 members of armed groups were 
killed during the last three day in Tlemcen, Boumerdes, Tizi 
Ouzou, and Blida. The same source said that during operations 
carried out by security forces considerable amounts of arms were 
seized. These included shotguns, Kalashnikov assault rifles, 
machine-guns, ammunition, and other equipment. 
  The communique said that during some of those operations 
five 
members of the security forces were slightly injured in the 
cross- fire with members of the armed groups in Bouguerra in 
Blida Province. 
  Another communique said that three secondary school girls, 
who were working as contact agents for an armed group, were 
arrested in the (Wannouaa) region in M'sila Province on 
Wednesday [25 May]. The same source said that a machine-gun, 
subversive documents, and a list containing security vehicles' 
license numbers were recovered following a search in one of the 
girls' abode. 
  Investigation revealed that the three pupils played the role 
of informer under the influence of their mathematics teacher. 
  The communique said that search was under way for this 
teacher who is still on the run. The three girls appeared 
before a court on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

