Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Firms To Settle Accounts With Ukrainian Partners in Rubles </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Firms To Settle Accounts With Ukrainian Partners in Rubles </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0205083694 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0205083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Industrialists from Belarus and Ukraine do not raise 
the issue of restoring the former political union. However, to 
normalize the (?functioning) of the two states' economies, 
industrialists consider it necessary to restore the former 
economic relations. The monetary merger agreement between 
Belarus and Russia is a key factor for the establishment of our 
relations with Ukraine. In this case, Belarusian enterprises 
will receive the opportunity to settle their accounts with their 
Ukrainian partners -- who buy raw materials from Russia -- in 
Russian rubles, which will naturally have a positive impact on 
the work of Belarusian enterprises. In general, in the opinion 
of experts, the preservation of close partnership-like relations 
will impart a vital impulse to the stabilization of the economic 
situation. 

</TEXT>

