  [Text] The edict of the presidium of the National Assembly 
of the Republic of Tajikistan on celebration of Victory Day: 
  (1) To permit holding festivities dedicated to Victory Day 
from 2 to 9 May 1994, as an exception in conditions of the state 
of emergency in Dushanbe city and other areas of the republic 
where the state of emergency is declared. 
  (2) The Ministries of Internal Affairs, Security, and 
Defense of the Republic of Tajikistan are to strictly ensure the 
public order and security and safety of citizens in the festive 
areas. 
  (3) The edict comes into force from the day of its issue. 
  [Signed] Emomali Rakhmonov, the Chairman of the National 
Assembly of the Republic of Tajikistan. 

