<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin on Need For Unity, Consolidation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin on Need For Unity, Consolidation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904174694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1640 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Goncharov] </F>
  [Text] Orenburg April 29 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin came here on Friday to participate in 
festivities on the occasion of the 250th anniversary of the 
Orenburg Province. 
  "Russia needs uniting and consolidating all forces now as 
never before - the fact is reflected in the treaty on social 
accord and we had to cover such a long way towards its signing," 
Chernomyrdin said. 
  "The government is to accept much of the responsibility for 
the fulfillment of the treaty and it will do its best. As a 
head of government, I am responsible for the fate of our 
homeland before the people and Russia. We shall overcome 
difficulties. We need (to turn Russia into) a country where a 
man will live happily. And the new Russia already takes shape," 
he added. 
  According to Chernomyrdin, he believes in his government and 
does not map out to replace or fire anyone; its political course 
remains unchanged. 
  The Russian prime minister visited a gas-processing plant 
and 
discussed ways to increase the volume of oil and gas extraction, 
use new and old bore-holes effectively, speed up the processing 
and secure the ties inside the fuel-and-energy complex. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60794 </DOCNO>
