<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governor Removed by Yeltsin Voted Duma Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Governor Removed by Yeltsin Voted Duma Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004034794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0300 GMT 
30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004034794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Eduard Rossel, the ex-governor of Sverdlovsk Oblast, 
has been elected chairman of the oblast Duma. Eighteen out of 
28 deputies voted for him. Rossel was dismissed from his post 
as governor by an edict of the Russian president in November 
1993 for overstepping the limits of his powers in connection 
with the proclaiming of the Urals Republic. Rossel considers 
switching over to a regional policy in the real sense the main 
priority of his work as the Duma chairman. This means the 
oblast being able to decide independently what to do with its 
material and financial resources and being the owner of its 
natural resources. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

