<H3> <TI>   Merger of Moscow, Moscow Oblast Said in Works </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Merger of Moscow, Moscow Oblast Said in Works </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK3004072094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 30 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK3004072094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["NG" report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Merger in the </F>
Cards Once Again"] 
  [Text] According to information NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA has 
received from sufficiently informed sources, there may soon 
appear a presidential edict on uniting Moscow and Moscow Oblast 
to form a single "Moscow Region." It is supposed to appoint as 
its head mayor of the capital Yuriy Luzhkov, who would also 
receive the rank of vice premier of the Russian Government. A 
draft of the edict is being prepared in corresponding 
subdivisions of City Hall, and Boris Yeltsin's agreement to sign 
it has virtually been secured, according to information from the 
same sources. Viktor Chernomyrdin, according to confidential 
information, does not like such plans. The reaction by Moscow 
Oblast administration head Anatoliy Tyazhlov is yet unknown. 

</TEXT>

