<F P=103> LD0105205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Employees of Ukraine's Security Service have 
conducted an operation in Mariupol to seize and expose a group 
of foreign citizens, who had intended to commit a terrorist act 
in Moscow. For this they had made powerful explosive devices 
with a long fragmentation range. Many of the details of the 
operation are for the moment not subject to publication. But, 
as Colonel Dmytro Chornousenko, deputy chief of Ukraine's 
Security Service directorate in Donetsk Oblast, stated, it has 
been established that the detainees had intended to carry out a 
terrorist act in one of the embassies located in Russia's 
capital. 

