<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Ulmanis Begin Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Ulmanis Begin Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004085794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0814 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Anna Melnikova, Yuriy </F>
Sizov] 
  [Text] Moscow 30 April TASS -- One-on-one negotiations 
between Boris Yeltsin and Latvian President guntis Ulmanis began 
in the Green Hall of the Grand Kremlin Palace. Ulmanis arrived 
for an official visit to Russia today. 
  Welcoming the distinquished Latvian guest Yeltsin noted that 
"this is the first official visit of a Latvian president to 
Russia." The Russian president said that "we have at last 
approached the landmark where we can reach a number of treaties 
and agreements, if not agree of all problems." 
  After the meeting in a narrow circle, the Russo-Latvian 
negotiations will continue in an enlarged composition. Taking 
part in the negotiations from the Russian side are Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev, Defence Minister Pavel Grachev and 
other officials. 
  The visit of the Baltic president has become a reality due 
to 
an arrangement reached at the bilateral negotiations to 
coordinate an additional protocol to the initialled document on 
social protection for Russian military pensioners living in 
Latvia, Sergey Zotov, head of the Russian delegation at the 
bilateral talks, told ITAR-TASS. 

</TEXT>

