  [Text] Moscow, 30 Apr -- Russia once again declares that it 
condemns the Stalinist repressions against independent Latvia, 
Boris Yeltsin said in the Kremlin today after the signing of a 
package of Russian-Latvian documents. 
  Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis thanked Boris Yeltsin for 
this gesture. For the inhabitants of Latvia these are very 
generous and fine words, which will help us to come to terms 
with many psychological contradictions that have been created 
during these decades, he said. 

