<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, Ireland's Spring Hold News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev, Ireland's Spring Hold News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904135994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1225 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Oleynyk] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 29 April TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and visiting Irish Deputy Prime Minister and 
Foreign Minister, Dick Spring, signed an intergovernment 
agreement on the prevention of double taxation on Friday. 
  During a news conference the Russian foreign minister said 
that a declaration on principles of relations between Russia and 
Ireland signed in Dublin last October was not merely an 
expression of their good intentions, but it was an important 
starting point for concrete work. Kozyrev pointed out the 
successful development of Russo-Irish ties at the level of 
concrete business-projects. "We have created a system of 
multi-stage political consultations on problems of the European 
and world politics," Kozyrev said, adding that he was grateful 
to Ireland for its assistance in finalizing an agreement on 
full- scale cooperation with the European Union. 
  Both Russian and Irish foreign ministers unanimously 
approved 
the level reached in the relations between the two countries, 
describing it as a very good and even excellent level and 
expressed confidence that bilateral relations would successfully 
develop. 

</TEXT>

