<H3> <TI>   Discusses Bosnia With Irish Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Bosnia With Irish Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1025 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Sergey Oleynik] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 29 Apr -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev has again called for the earliest possible meeting on 
Bosnia with the participation of Russia, the United States, the 
European Union [EU], and the United Nations. Such a meeting 
"would help to consolidate the approaches" of the interested 
sides, he said at a news conference following talks here with 
Dick Spring, the Irish foreign minister. A. Kozyrev stressed 
the role of the EU in settling the Bosnian conflict, which he 
described as "a key factor." 
  As a representative of an EU member country, the Irish 
minister supported the proposal to urgently sit down at the 
negotiating table. "Once we get down to directly discussing the 
problem it won't be so difficult to reach a common international 
position," D. Spring noted, replying to an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent's question on the closeness of the approaches of 
Russia and the EU to this regional conflict. 

</TEXT>

