<H3> <TI>   Churkin Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin Holds News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904150494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1353 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Pshenichnikov] </F>
  [Text] Oslo, 29 Apr -- Consultations held here today were 
devoted to a discussion of the initiative put forward the other 
day by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev to hold a meeting 
of the heads of the foreign policy departments of the United 
States, Russia, and other "key countries" in order to work out 
ways of settling the crisis in Bosnia. They were attended by 
Deputy foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin, the Russian president's 
special envoy, and Thorvald Stoltenberg and Lord Owen, the 
cochairmen of the coordinating committee of the international 
conference on the former Yugoslavia. 
  At a news conference on the results of the consultations, it 
was stated that the forthcoming meeting of foreign ministers of 
the United States, Russia, and other "key countries" was 
intended to coordinate the efforts of the world community to end 
the war in Bosnia. The parties to the Bosnian conflict will not 
be invited to the meeting. 

</TEXT>

