<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leader of Russia's Liberal Democratic party 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is planning to leave Moscow on 8 May for 
Belgrade. 
  The press secretary of the Liberal Democratic faction in the 
Russian State Duma Grigoriy Serebrennikov says that Zhirinovskiy 
will be accompanied by a deputy chairman of both the Liberal 
Democratic party and the State Duma Aleksandr Vengerovskiy and 
Liberal Democrats who are either doing active duty or are 
retired servicemen. 
  According to Serebrennikov, the Zhirinovskiy delegation will 
be expected to hold consultations with Bosnia's Serb leaders. 

