<DOCNO> FBIS4-60850 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov084_p_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-084 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Areas Shelled 1 May, Casualties Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Areas Shelled 1 May, Casualties Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205101494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0955 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan, 2 May -- May Day evening and overnight was 
unsettled on Armenia's borders. The border zone village of 
Koti, Noyemberyanskiy Rayon, in northeast Armenia was subjected 
to mortars, artillery, and machine-gun fire from 1845 hours 
until late in the night from the adjacent Azerbaijani territory, 
the ITAR-TASS correspondent was told today at the republic's 
Defense Ministry press center. The village of Artanish in the 
Krasnoselskiy Rayon of Armenia was fired on starting from 2200 
hours. There have been casualties. 

</TEXT>

