<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Offers To Promote Karabakh Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    France Offers To Promote Karabakh Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004121794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1027 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Shtorkh] </F>
  [Text] Paris April 30 TASS -- France is ready to promote 
the quest for a peace settlement in Nagorno-Karabakh if the 
Armenian and the Azeri sides wish so. French Foreign Minister 
Alain Juppe said this here on Friday during a meeting with his 
Armenian counterpart Vahan Papazyan. Juppe said France had 
always been in favour of solution to the Nagorno-Karabakh 
conflict in the framework of the Conference on Security and 
Cooperation in Europe (CSCE). 
  The ministers noted with satisfaction that there are no 
contradictions in Franco-Armenian bilateral relations. Juppe 
confirmed that the draft law envisaging the ratification of the 
agreement on friendship between France and Armenia will be put 
on the agenda of the spring session of the National Assembly now 
underway in France. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

