<F P=106> [News department report: "News From the Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs"] 
  [Text] An official opening ceremony of the Republic of 
Armenia Embassy in Romania was held on 24 April in Bucharest. 
Among those present were Armenian Minister of Foreign Affairs 
Vahan Papazyan; Armenian Ambassador to Romania Georgi Kazinyan; 
Romania's Secretary of State Ioan Mircea Pascu; and heads of 
foreign diplomatic representations accredited to Romania. The 
embassy was blessed by the head of the Armenian congregation in 
Romania and Bulgaria, Archbishop Tirayr Martikyan. 
<H8>  * * * </H8>
  On 25 April, Zhirayr Liparutyan, Armenia's first deputy 
minister of foreign affairs, received the Netherlands ambassador 
to Russia and Armenia, Baron de Vos Van Steenwijk. In the course 
of the meeting, they exchanged opinions regarding development of 
bilateral relations, the situation in the region, and the 
efforts of Armenian leadership in the matter of resolving the 
Karabakh conflict. 

</TEXT>

