<H3> <TI>   Armenia To Join International Communications Network </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenia To Join International Communications Network </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904210394 Yerevan SNARK in English 1409 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2904210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, April 29 (SNARK) -- The Yerevan center of 
the Armenian National Network of Data Transmission will allow 
Armenia to establish communication with 100 National centers in 
42 countries of the world, members of the Association of 
International Communications. 
  The Center, which will be opened by the end of May, will 
allow the 5 largest Armenian cities to receive and send 
information by fax, telex, teletype and E-mail by means of 
satellite communication. Afterwards, other settlements of 
Armenia will join the network. 
  The press-service of the Armenian government told SNARK the 
Prime Minister Grant Bagratyan visited the Center today. Among 
other questions there was discussed a possibility of joining the 
network by the state banks, which will allow to create a united 
center of bank information. 

</TEXT>

