<H3> <TI>   Deputy Speaker Denies Rumors of Interethnic Tensions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Speaker Denies Rumors of Interethnic Tensions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904202394 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2904202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In recent days some provocateurs and press organs 
are claiming that the interethnic relations in our republic's 
northern region have again become aggravated. Our colleague 
Gulsefa Ahmedova interviewed Deputy Chairman of the Supreme 
Soviet Afiaddin Dzhalilov. 
  [Begin Dzhalilov recording] I believe that these are mere 
rumors and are provocative in nature. With a group of 
parliamentarians we visited [word indistinct] (?Siazen), 
Khachmasskiy, Kubanskiy, and Kusarskiy Rayons in recent days. 
We met the local inhabitants. Of course we also met with the 
Lezghins living in Kusarkiy. I can state unequivocally that the 
Lezghin people and all the peoples living in that region are 
involved in Azerbaijan's life, are doing everything for the 
speedy resolution of the Karabakh problem, and the Azerbaijani 
and Lezghin peoples, who have lived and created together in that 
same place, are sparing nothing in this grave historic, 
political, military, and economic period for Azerbaijan. The 
conclusion at these meetings was that human rights in Azerbaijan 
are being protected, every suitable condition is being created 
for national minorities, and the national minorities in 
Azerbaijan, including the Russian community, share Azerbaijani 
people's cares and are resolved to see a speedy end to this war 
and the Armenian aggression, and a peaceful resolution of the 
Karabakh problem. 
  In a word, I want to say that no matter if they are 
Lezghins, 
or Russians, or other ethnic minorities living in Azerbaijan, 
they state unequivocally in connection with our visit there that 
they support Azerbaijan President Geydar Aliyev's political 
activity. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

