<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Referring to the Georgian head of state's press 
service, the CONTACT news agency reports that yesterday, 
Georgian head of state Eduard Shevardnadze met Operia Mindit, a 
director of a group of Indian companies, and representatives of 
Georgian business circles. 
  The conversation touched upon issues of establishing and 
developing economic cooperation between Georgia and India. The 
visitors said that it would be advisable if a Georgian 
representation and an Indian-Georgian center for trade, culture, 
and friendship opened in India. The conversation also touched 
upon credits to be allotted as humanitarian aid, cooperation in 
the spheres of sea and air transport, as well as [word 
indistinct] and food production. 
  Shevardnadze thanked the visitors for the interest they 
demonstrated toward Georgia and said that relations between 
Georgia and India have centuries-long traditions. Prospects for 
the extension of the relations have now emerged. 

