<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Presents Draft of Territorial System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Presents Draft of Territorial System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0105154994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1209 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0105154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Georgia's Constitutional Commission worked out the 
draft of political and territorial system for the country, a 
member of the Commission told Interfax. The draft provides for 
dividing Georgia into 12 territories, Abkhazia and Ajaria among 
them, though with a special political status. This provision 
does not relate to South Ossetia. 
  In the meantime, as Interfax learned from reliable sources, 
the Georgian leadership is planning to hold talks with the 
present South Ossetian administration concerning the political 
status of that territory. On instructions from Eduard 
Shevardnadze a special group was formed to conduct these talks. 
The talks are to take place in mid May. 

</TEXT>

