<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays Threatens Disclosures on Privatization Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chubays Threatens Disclosures on Privatization Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904175594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1057 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 29 Apr -- Viktor Ilyukhin, chairman of the 
State Duma Committee on Security, will, after the spring 
parliamentary recess, make public documentary evidence in his 
possession of infringements of privatization regulations by the 
State Committee for the Management of State Property. He told 
this to an ITAR-TASS correspondent in a telephone conversation 
today. 
  Viktor Ilyukhin is unperturbed by the news that Anatoliy 
Chubays has decided to bring a court action against him for 
slander. "As a lawyer," he underlined, "I judge the documents I 
have collected to be very serious. They show convincingly that 
the methods which Anatoliy Chubays is using to carry out the 
transfer of state property into private hands serve the 
interests of only 15 to 20 percent of Russia's population." 
  Without waiting for the court to consider, the chairman of 
the Duma Security Committee has decided to inform press 
representatives of the contents of these documents on 
approximately 11-12 May -- immediately after the end of the 
lower chamber of parliament's recess. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

