<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Approves Research Program for Legal System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Approves Research Program for Legal System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004183294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president has issued a decree approving a 
program to conduct complex political and legal research in 
1994-95 on ways and forms of strengthening the Russian state. 
The program has been developed by workers of the Institute of 
State and Law of the Russian Academy of Sciences. 
  Boris Yeltsin has also sanctioned the main directions of 
this 
research. They include six sections, of which the priority one 
is the development of the legal system of the Russian Federation 
after the adoption of the new constitution. In particular, an 
idea has been advanced concerning the setting up of a unified 
humanitarian space over the territory of the former Soviet 
Union, which will guarantee protection of the rights of the 
Russophone population in the former Soviet republics and will 
help settle the issue of forced emigration. 

</TEXT>

