<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy To Bring Legal Action Against Press </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy To Bring Legal Action Against Press </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904163594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1513 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 29 TASS -- Leader of the Russian 
Liberal- Democratic Party Vladimir Zhirinovskiy plans to bring 
an action against Vice-Premier Anatoliy Chubays and a number of 
newspapers. 
  His lawyer Sergey Belyak has prepared a "new set of suits" 
to 
protect the honor and dignity of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, says a 
report of the Liberal-Democratic faction's press service 
circulated here today. 
  In the opinion of Zhirinovskiy, the newspapers SEGODNYA, 
KURANTY and IZVESTIYA are guilty "of spreading German media's 
fake report on alleged reception of Honecker money by the 
Liberal-Democratic Party". The lawyer is sure each newspaper 
will have "to pay at least 200 million rubles". 
  The reason for the action against Chubays is his accusations 
of Zhirinovskiy of fascism. The report says the last straw was 
Chubays' interview with the ARGUMENTY I FAKTY newspaper. 

</TEXT>

