<F P=106> [Maksim Isayev report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Charges </F>
Brought Against a High-Ranking Internal Affairs Ministry 
Official?"] 
  [Text] Your NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA correspondent has learned 
from knowledgeable sources that at the end of last week a 
criminal lawsuit was filed against Militia General I.A. Shilov, 
deputy chief of the Internal Affairs Ministry's Main Criminal 
Investigations Administration, on charges of his alleged ties 
with criminals. As a measure of preventive restriction, he 
signed a written undertaking not to abscond. At the same time, 
a number of other high-ranking Internal Affairs Ministry 
officials have been detained in connection with the case. 
  At the Internal Affairs Ministry Public Relations Center 
they 
have told NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA that they do not know anything 
about the matter. 

</TEXT>

