<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Wants Elections Postponed, Comments on Chernobyl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Wants Elections Postponed, Comments on Chernobyl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904111394 Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA in Ukrainian 29 Apr 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2904111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [UKRINFORM report: "The President Has Confirmed His </F>
Intention"] 
  [Text] The Ukrainian president met with the collective of 
KIYEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI, familiarized himself with the 
technological process of preparing the newspaper, and answered 
journalists' questions. Leonid Kravchuk confirmed his intention 
not to take part in the presidential elections. He will stand 
up in the parliament for their postponement. The president 
expressed a hope that the new Supreme Council would support him. 
"This is not just my opinion. Dozens of local councils, 
hundreds of labor collectives, and some political parties spoke 
in favor of postponing the elections," stressed the head of the 
Ukrainian state. 
  Touching upon the further operation of the Chernobyl Atomic 
Electric Power Plant, the president pointed out: All conditions 
have been created for its normal work. There can be no question 
of closing it down now because, first, there are no funds for 
that and, second, Ukraine has found itself in an energy crisis. 

</TEXT>

