<H3> <TI>   Deputies Collect Signatures To Postpone Presidential Race </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputies Collect Signatures To Postpone Presidential Race </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2904125794 Kiev KIYEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI in Russian 28 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> WS2904125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev KIYEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vladimir Katsman: "More Than a Third of Deputies </F>
Are Against 26 June Elections"] 
  [Text] As a KIYEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI correspondent has learned 
from sources close to the Supreme Council, a group of newly 
elected deputies began to collect signatures demanding 
postponement of the presidential and local elections. According 
to preliminary assessments, as of the evening of 26 April, the 
group collected 130 signatures. The list, however, is not yet 
closed -- the collection of signatures continues. Having 
obtained the support of a third of the deputies, the initiators 
of this action continue to pursue their goal. 
  The same sources have reported that the number of 
signatories 
increased after Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk had revealed 
his intention to ask the Supreme Council to change its 
resolution on the summer elections. There is another very 
interesting fact. Among deputies who have signed the motion, 
are those who are affiliated to entirely opposing teams of 
candidates for the presidency, including teams which consider 
the elections absolutely essential. 

</TEXT>

