<H3> <TI>   National Guard Contingent in Crimea Strengthened </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Guard Contingent in Crimea Strengthened </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904193894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1931 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A source in the Interior Ministry of the Ukrainian 
autonomous republic of Crimea told INTERFAX that Ukraine had in 
the last few days increased its National Guard contingent in the 
Crimean capital Simferopol. 
  But the ministry does not know exactly how many National 
Guards are currently stationed in the city, the source said. 
  However, other sources in Simferopol said there are more 
than 
2,500 National Guards in the city, which is being patrolled by 
details of four or five National Guards with truncheons, an 
officer and several armed police. 

</TEXT>

