<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Factory To Reopen Inside Chernobyl Exclusion Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Factory To Reopen Inside Chernobyl Exclusion Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004090394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0730 GMT 30 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian cabinet of ministers has decided on 
resuming work at one of the enterprises in the town of Pripet, 
which is located inside the 30 km exclusion zone around the 
Chernobyl nuclear power station. This decision was made in 
connection with the need to provide for the functioning of 
Ukraine's nuclear power industry and meet its requirements for 
spares and nonstandard equipment. Work at Pripet's industrial 
enterprises was halted on 26 April 1986 -- the day of the 
disaster at Chernobyl nuclear power station. 

</TEXT>

