<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester, Moldova Leaders Outline Conflict Resolutions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester, Moldova Leaders Outline Conflict Resolutions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004144194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1341 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Fedor Angeliy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] April 30 TASS -- Moldavian 
[Moldovan] President Mircea Snegur and Dniester Republic leader 
Igor Smirnov made a joint statement on Saturday outlining ways 
to resolve the Dniester conflict. 
  The statement signed in presence of representatives of the 
Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe (CSCE) and 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin's envoys said that a new social 
and political situation has emerged in the republic, creating 
prerequisites for successful resolution of the crisis. 
  Both leaders welcomed the mediatory role of CSCE and the 
Russian Federation in settling the Dniester conflict. 
  Snegur and Smirnov stressed the need to determine the status 
of the Dniester Republic, establish official relations, delegate 
and delineate powers and fix up a transitional period for 
gradual implementation of reached agreements in all spheres. 
  The document also calls for establishing firm guarantees, 
including with international participation, ensuring full and 
unconditional implementation of these agreements. 

</TEXT>

