<H3> <TI>   Latvian President Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latvian President Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004080994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0719 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 30 April TASS -- Latvian President Guntis 
Ulmanis arrived in Moscow today to meet Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin. 
  The visit of the Latvian president has materialised due to 
the agreement reached at the Russo-Latvian negotiations to 
coordinate an additional protocol to the earlier initialled 
document -- on social protection for military pensioners living 
in Latvia. The package of bilateral agreements will be 
discussed at negotiations of the two presidents in the Kremlin. 
  The visit of Guntis Ulmanis to Moscow planned for an earlier 
timeframe was put off because of the stance of the Latvian Sejm. 
Deputies did not want the package of agreements to include the 
above-mentioned document on social guarantees for retired 
military. The Russian side insisted on the discussion of all the 
four agreements, including Russian troop withdrawal from Latvia, 
the status of the radar in Skrunda, social protection for the 
military during the troop withdrawal and guarantees for military 
pensioners. President Yeltsin succeeded in clearing the obstacle 
to the summit. 

</TEXT>

