<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs Edict To Streamline Use of Foreign Labor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Signs Edict To Streamline Use of Foreign Labor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1328 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow April 30 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin signed a decree on Friday to streamline the use of 
foreign labour in Russia and ensure the priority right of 
Russian citizens to fill vacancies. 
  The document expands the December 16, 1993 decree on the use 
of foreign labour in Russia to cover foreign legal entities 
operating in Russia under contracts. The new regulations will 
not apply to those organisations which send employees to Russia 
to install their equipment. 

</TEXT>

