<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Party Condemns Snegur-Smirnov Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Party Condemns Snegur-Smirnov Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3004194494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1800 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3004194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 29/4/1994 -- "The declaration 
of Moldovan and Dniester leaders," signed by Mircea Snegur and 
Igor Smirnov on April 28th, "is another step of the process of 
Bessarabia's subjugation to Russian interests," states the 
declaration of the Christian-Democratic Popular Front of Moldova 
[FPCDM]. According to it, "Moscow representatives who hold the 
key posts in Moldova seriously injured our national interests 
and undermined Moldova's independence and unity" with this new 
agreement between Chisinau and Tiraspol. The April 28th 
declaration implies official recognition of the "Dniester 
Moldovan Republic" which is considered synonymous with Moldova. 
The declaration says that the presence of the CSCE mission at 
this meeting mars the prestige of this international 
organization and makes "it an advocate of Russian imperial 
policy." The FPCDM "considers that the deal on April 28th aims 
at annulling the national unified state and jeopardizes the 
nation's fundamental right to self-determination," concludes the 
declaration. 

</TEXT>

