<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation to Hungary Discusses Cooperation Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation to Hungary Discusses Cooperation Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205100394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A visit to Budapest by an official Kazakh delegation 
led by Deputy Foreign Minister Konstantin Zhigalov was devoted 
to examination of the possibilities to deepen and broaden 
political and economic integration between Hungary and 
Kazakhstan. The guests from Almaty visited one of the largest 
Hungarian enterprises -- the Videoton joint stock production 
amalgamation, whose products are well known on the former USSR 
market. The Kazakh delegation was interested first of all in 
the progress of privatization of large Hungarian enterprises, in 
the level of involvement of working collectives in this process. 
  According to one of the leaders of Videoton, Peter Lakotosz, 
his enterprise has begun to establish close links with 
Kazakhstan. Hungarian foreign policy pays increasing attention 
to the development of ties with the Asian republics of the 
former USSR which have gained their independence, said Andras 
Kelemen, political state secretary of the Hungarian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs. He stressed that during this visit a framework 
for a joint agreement aimed at strengthening Kazakh-Hungarian 
ties in all fields will be discussed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

