<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fire at Thermoelectric Plant Brings Industry to Near Halt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fire at Thermoelectric Plant Brings Industry to Near Halt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205092694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0700 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Southern Kazakhstan's biggest thermoelectric plant, 
the Chimkent Thermoelectric-3 Plant, has stopped working after 
the failure of one of the pumps caused the plant's cable network 
to burn out. It took about three hours to put out the fire. 
The accident has practically brought to a halt two industrial 
giants -- a tyre factory and an oil refinery. Work is under way 
to clear up the accident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

