<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-084 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Issues Statement on Tajikistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Issues Statement on Tajikistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004102494 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 2300 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry of Kyrgyzstan has circulated a 
statement: The first round of talks on interethnic 
reconciliation in Tajikistan has taken place in Moscow. It was 
held under the auspices of the United Nations. Attending it 
were observers from Kazakhstan, Iran, Afghanistan, Kyrgyzstan, 
Pakistan, Uzbekistan and Russia. The sides [word indistinct] a 
special address from the UN secretary general, agreed on and 
signed a joint declaration which urges the government of 
Tajikistan and the opposition forces to restrain from any kind 
of activities which might endanger the negotiating process. 
  A protocol was signed by the sides involved on setting up a 
joint commission which will address issues of refugees and 
migrants from Tajikistan. Kyrgyzstan considers the aspiration 
of its participants to establish a political dialogue as an 
important result of the talks. The republic regards it as the 
only way for achieving national accord. Kyrgyzstan, as well as 
other CIS participants, expressed its concern with the situation 
on the Tajik-Afghan border still being tense. Kyrgyzstan is 
Tajikistan's nearest neighbor and therefore it cannot remain 
indifferent to the situation which has developed there. 
Kyrgyzstan in its foreign policy is guided by the principle of 
noninterference in the affairs of Tajikistan as a sovereign 
state and develops cooperation with it in accordance with the 
accepted norms of international law, the UN Charter, and 
Kyrgyzstan's liabilities as the CIS member-state. Kyrgyzstan 
pursues the policy of supporting peace-making efforts by 
international organizations and the CIS countries aimed at 
stabilizing the situation in Tajikistan. 
  Kyrgyzstan stands for further developing of friendly 
cooperation with the Republic of Tajikistan, and recognizes its 
government which has been elected in accordance with the 
Constitution. Kyrgyzstan always spoke in favor of holding a 
political dialogue between the government of Tajikistan and the 
opposition. It would have created conditions for overcoming the 
developed conflict situation and national reconciliation in 
Tajikistan. 
  The Foreign Ministry of Kyrgyzstan supports the aspiration 
of 
the participants of the talks to develop the negotiating process 
with the aim of achieving national accord. Kyrgyzstan is sure 
that there are possibilities for political settlement of the 
situation in Tajikistan, normalization of the situation on the 
Tajik-Afghan border. All the sides involved should show their 
good will. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60958 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov084_l_94002" </HT>


