<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agree on Closer Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agree on Closer Economic Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205084894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0745 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Maynayev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek, 2 May -- The presidents of Kazakhstan, 
Kyrgyzstan, and Uzbekistan devoted their meeting on 29-30 April 
on the shore of Lake Issyk-Kul to the deepening of economic 
links in Central Asia and the CIS, says a communique on the 
results of the summit meeting released today by President Askar 
Akayev's press service. 
  The document notes that the meeting was held in a spirit of 
mutual understanding and trust. The sides exchanged views on 
the current situation in the region and the Commonwealth, and 
also on a whole range of international problems. 
  The presidents of the three countries signed a treaty on the 
creation of a single economic space, representing a new level of 
integration for the economies of the Central Asian states, the 
communique stresses. The sides noted that the time has come to 
remove all the obstacles standing in the way of economic 
interaction and to eliminate customs barriers, double taxation, 
and complications with the passage of payments; and that the 
treaty is fully in accordance with the provisions of the 
agreement on the creation of a CIS economic union, and is open 
for joining by all the states of the Commonwealth. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60965 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov085cc_94004" </HT>


