<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205100294 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] As has already been reported, a summit of the 
Presidents of Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, and Uzbekistan took place 
in Karakol. Such summits have become traditional. [passage 
omitted] The main result of this meeting is Kyrgyzstan's joining 
the agreement on a common economic space between Kazakhstan and 
Uzbekistan. Now this is a tripartite agreement. [passage 
omitted] The presidents said that this agreement represents a 
new level of economic integration of the Central Asian states. 
There will be no obstacles, such as customs barriers, double 
taxation. Currency exchange points will be opened. Steps taken 
by the governments to improve goods turnover and goods exchange 
as well as regulation of labor inflow and outflow between the 
states will positively influence the economic situation in the 
region. Further enhancement of economic cooperation will lead 
to a better mechanism, which will facilitate constructive 
interaction and help resolve a number of political problems that 
are common in the region as well. It concerns efficient, 
mutually beneficial and peaceful co-habitation of different 
ethnic groups in Central Asia, which will become a stabilizing 
factor of the ethnic situation in the region. The participants 
of the meeting expressed their readiness to continue their 
search for new forms of interstate cooperation in the interests 
of the three nations. 
  Within the framework of the CIS summit decisions to render 
help to Kyrgyzstan, the presidents discussed concrete measures 
to be taken in order to eliminate damage inflicted on the Kyrgyz 
economy by recent mud slides. The presidents expressed their 
satisfaction with the fruitful talks and their hope for these 
talks to further stimulate friendship and cooperation in the 
region. [words indistinct] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

