<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Premier Proposes Collective CIS Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Premier Proposes Collective CIS Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0205153994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 30 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0205153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Bablumyan: "Armenian Premier Proposes CIS </F>
Countries Institute Collective Currency"] 
  [Text] Yerevan -- Armenian Prime Minister Hrant Bagratian 
has sent a letter to all the CIS prime ministers. 
  It states, in particular, that financial transactions 
between 
the CIS countries have become considerably more complex as a 
result of the introduction of national currencies. The Russian 
ruble is used as a single currency for many trade deals between 
states; the CIS countries look to Russia for loans to execute 
their transactions, thereby increasing the Russian budget 
deficit. The prime minister thinks that the way to ease 
financial difficulties lies in the broader use of national 
currencies, and also proposes setting up a collective currency 
for the CIS countries, in which it is proposed to carry out all 
transactions in a CIS interstate bank. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

