<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chuvashia Introduces Tax Measures To Improve Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chuvashia Introduces Tax Measures To Improve Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205213694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1920 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent L. Nikitin, including recorded </F>
remarks by I. Mironov, economics minister of the Chuvash 
Republic of the Russian Federation; from the "Vesti" newscast] 
  [Text] Chuvashia is trying to overcome the economic crisis 
by relying on its own potential. Our correspondent reports: 
  [Nikitin] Chuvash Republic President Nikolay Fedorov has 
signed an edict on additional measures to settle economic 
relations in the Republic. 
  [Mironov] We are faced with two main tasks today. First, to 
help republican goods producers to overcome their difficult 
situation. The second task is of a more strategic nature; it is 
to turn the Chuvash Republic into a major business, cultural, 
economic, and financial center of the Volga region. 
  [Nikitin] The edict stipulates a lower tax rate applicable 
to 
banking. The republican authorities believe that the Chuvash 
capital of Cheboksary will become one of Russia's major banking 
centers. Goods producers should already be given assistance in 
creating investment resources. Privileges are being introduced 
by the edict with respect to some taxes, including the tax on 
profits on enterprises engaged in production that are being set 
up in the republic. They are exempt from this tax for three 
years, which is quite a sufficient period for an enterprise to 
establish itself and start production. After this, the 
enterprise can fulfill its obligations to society and start 
paying taxes. Thus, mutual interests will be satisfied. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

