<H3> <TI>   Vyatka River Shipping Season Resumes; Workload Way Down </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vyatka River Shipping Season Resumes; Workload Way Down </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0205165794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 30 Apr 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM0205165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Shipping Season on River"] </F>
  [Text] The first ships traveled down the Vyatka River 28 
April, starting timber logging. Shipment of grain and 
construction materials is next in line. 
  In the whole shipping season, the crews of the Vyatka River 
Steamship Company have to ship around 2 million tonnes of 
freight. That is considerably less than in past years. 
Customers' inability to pay has robbed the enterprise of a 
chance of procuring the full amount of fuel. Some of the fleet 
will therefore be standing idle. However, passenger lines will 
open in time as planned and in a day or two the first motor 
ships will set out. 

</TEXT>

