<H3> <TI>   Germany To Assist in Re-Equipping Nuclear Power Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Germany To Assist in Re-Equipping Nuclear Power Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205171394 Lvov ZA VILNU UKRAYINU in Ukrainian 26 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> AU0205171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lvov ZA VILNU UKRAYINU </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Germany Will Supply Equipment as Aid </F>
to the Rivne Nuclear Power Station"] 
  [Text] By the end of 1995, the Rivne Nuclear Power Station 
will receive equipment worth 21 million German marks from 
Germany. This was agreed upon during a meeting at the nuclear 
facility between representatives of the Society for the Safety 
of Nuclear Reactors and of the German firms "Siemens," "ABB," 
and "Lloyd." 
  Following the interstate agreement, the German side will 
provide equipment for the periodic inspection of metals and 
diagnostics, telecommunications equipment, and fire-proof 
materials. This will make it possible to modernize the 
functioning power unit with its output of 1 million 
kilowatt/hours. Assembly operations will be carried out by 
Rivne nuclear specialists with the help of specialists from 
various German companies assigned by the Society for the Safety 
of Nuclear Reactors, taking into account their experience in 
organizing and implementing measures to increase nuclear safety. 

</TEXT>

