<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazakhstan, Saudi Arabia To Establish Diplomatic Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazakhstan, Saudi Arabia To Establish Diplomatic Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205164094 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Kanat Saudabayev paid an 
official visit to Saudi Arabia from 29 April to 2 May. He was 
received by His Majesty King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud. 
The foreign minister gave President Nazarbayev's personal 
letter to the king. The king expressed sincere gratitude and 
asked Saudabayev to convey his respect to the Kazakh leader. 
The king highly assessed Nazarbayev's efforts to reform society 
and the economy, to preserve peace and stability in Central 
Asia, and to strengthen security in the region. The king 
invited Nazarbayev to pay an official visit to Saudi Arabia. 
  Kanat Saudabayev met Saudi Foreign Minister Sa'ud al-Faysal 
Bin- 'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud. They discussed broadening 
bilateral relations and other regional and international issues 
of mutual interest. Kazakhstan and Saudi Arabia expressed their 
readiness to develop political, economic, and other relations. 
[passage omitted] The ministers signed a protocol on 
establishing diplomatic relations at embassy level, and they 
intend to take appropriate measures to develop friendly 
cooperation. Thus, Foreign Minister Sa'ud al-Faysal 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud will pay a return visit to Almaty 
shortly. Saudabayev also met the Saudi oil, trade, and planning 
ministers and the head of the development fund and discussed 
future economic and trade cooperation. The two countries agreed 
to exchanged trade delegations in the near future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

