<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Guards Prevent `Armed Provocations' on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Guards Prevent `Armed Provocations' on Afghan Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305073594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0706 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305073594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe 3 May TASS -- Russian borderguards have 
prevented one more armed provocation on the Pamir stretch of the 
Tajik-Afghan border. 
  ITAR-TASS today learned at the headquarters of the Russian 
borderguard troops in Tajikistan that a group of armed men from 
the Tajik opposition made a attempt on Monday evening to fight 
their way into Tajikistan on one of the sectors guarded by the 
Horog borderguard detachment. 
  The intruders enjoyed fire coverage from Afghan territory. 
The Russian borderguards were compelled to retaliate, thereby 
preventing the gang from crossing the border river. The Russian 
troops suffered no casualties. The enemy losses were not 
reported. 
  Men of the irreconcilable opposition are now being massed on 
separate sections of the border between Tajikistan and the 
Afghan province of Tahor. Military sources do not rule out new 
armed provocations on this stretch of the border. 

</TEXT>

