<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nagorno-Karabakh Statement on Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nagorno-Karabakh Statement on Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1157A Yerevan RESPUBLIKA ARMENIYA in Russian 29 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> 944K1157A </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan RESPUBLIKA ARMENIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Message "To the Ministry of Defense of the Russian </F>
Federation, P. Grachev, and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of 
the Russian Federation, A. Kozyrev, and V. Kazimirov" published 
under the rubric "Artsakh": "The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Is 
Prepared To Provide for Complete Cease-Fire"] 
  [Text] The leaders of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic, having 
accepted the proposal of the Russian Federation and confirming 
their readiness for peaceful regulation of the armed conflict 
between the Armenian Republic and the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic, 
agree to provide for a complete cease-fire and to end combat 
activities as of 0001 hours on 29 April 1994 in keeping with the 
Protocol of 18 February 1994. 
  Taking into account the absence of observers and the mutual 
mistrust of the opposing sides and striving to preclude possible 
attempts to take advantage of the temporary respite to prepare 
for another large-scale attack and thus, contribute to the 
irreversibility of the peace process, the leadership of the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic considers it necessary to set in 
motion the entire mechanism of the aforementioned Protocol 
signed by the parties to the conflict with the participation of 
the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation. 
  Only the realization of this complex of envisioned 
military-technical measures can guarantee stable termination of 
combat activities and create favorable conditions for solving 
the political programs. 
  The leaders of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic are prepared to 
issue the corresponding orders after the intermediary confirms 
the receipt of the identical document from the opposing side. 
  [Signed] Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Nagorno-Karabakh 
Republic A. Gukasyan 
  [Signed] Commander of the Army for Defense of the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic S. Babayan 
  Stepanakert, 28 April 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

