<H3> <TI>   Ter-Petrosyan, Nagorno-Karabakh Leaders Meet in Goris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ter-Petrosyan, Nagorno-Karabakh Leaders Meet in Goris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205182594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1600 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Kirghizia [Kyrgyzstan], a meeting of the working 
groups of the Interparliamentary Assembly of the CIS on problems 
of a settlement of the Karabakh conflict begins today. Speakers 
of the parliaments of Azerbaijan, Armenia, and Russia and 
representatives of Nagornyy Karabakh have begun arriving in 
Bishkek. Our commentator on the situation on the eve of the 
meeting: 
  [Correspondent A. Ivanova] The Armenian leadership headed by 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan held consultations today in the 
town of Goris with the leadership of Nagornyy Karabakh 
[Nagorno-Karabakh]. The details of the conversation are not 
being disclosed. According to unofficial information, the sides 
discussed the approach to a settlement of the Karabakh conflict 
in connection with the meeting planned for 3 May in Bishkek of 
heads of parliaments of Armenia and Azerbaijan, with the 
participation of representatives of Nagornyy Karabakh. 
  The initiator of the meeting was the CIS Interparliamentary 
Assembly, which has noticeably stepped up its peacemaking 
activity in the zone of the Karabakh conflict. 
  Vladimir Shumeyko, who arrived in Bishkek today, stated that 
the talks provide an opportunity to reach agreement on the 
question of a settlement of the Karabakh conflict. He considers 
the main justification for this to be the fact that Azerbaijan 
recognized Nagornyy Karabakh recently as one of the participants 
of this conflict. Shumeyko called this a very big leap forward 
in the process of the talks on Karabakh. 

</TEXT>

