<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gasanov Sets Conditions for Karabakh Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gasanov Sets Conditions for Karabakh Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0205173394 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0205173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report from our Foreign Ministry's press 
service: 
  To ensure the irreversibility of the peace talks, 
Azerbaijan, 
Armenia, and the international organizations, primarily the 
CSCE, should declare that they will assume the following 
obligations after the establishment of a cease-fire in the 
region. 
  1. The Armenian Republic's leadership should guarantee to 
pull out its Armed Forces from all the occupied Azerbaijani 
lands, including Shusha and Lachin. 
  2. The Azerbaijani Republic's leadership should guarantee to 
discuss Daghlyk-Karabakh's [Nagorno-Karabakh's] status within 
the Azerbaijani state structure. 
  3. The CSCE countries should announce that they will not 
allow military equipment to be sent to Daghlyk-Karabakh. 
  This proposal was put forward by our republic's foreign 
minister, Gasan Gasanov, during a meeting with Mathias Mosberg, 
deputy chairman of Minsk Group. 

</TEXT>

