<H3> <TI>   Minister Briefs EU Envoys on Law on Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Briefs EU Envoys on Law on Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205161994 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1400 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry's press service has reported to 
Estonian Radio that Foreign Minister Juri Luik had a meeting 
today with ambassadors of the European Union [EU], at their 
request. The ambassadors voiced concern over some practical 
aspects of the implementation of the law on foreigners. At the 
same time, it was emphasized once again the the EU accepts the 
Estonian law on foreigners and its legal logic. 
  The ambassadors who attended the meeting noted that the EU's 
position on troop withdrawal remains the same, which means that 
the Russian troops must leave Estonia unconditionally by 31 
August. The EU has also notified the Russian Federation of this 
position. 
  Juri Luik provided a progress report about the registration 
of aliens as well as about reorganization of the citizenship and 
immigration department. 

</TEXT>

