<H3> <TI>   Swedish Justice Ministry Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Swedish Justice Ministry Delegation Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205170094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1600 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As reported to ETA by the Estonian Justice Ministry, 
a 12-strong delegation of the Swedish Justice Ministry is 
visiting Tallinn today. According to Imbi Markus, the head of 
the ministry's foreign relations department, the delegation 
consists mainly of (?clerical) staff and financial and 
administrative managers. According to Markus, this visit is 
linked to preparations for a meeting to map out an extensive 
cooperation project between the two ministries. 
  Today, a basic agreement on cooperation between Estonian and 
Swedish postal services was signed. This will be followed by 
the conclusion of a string of agreements on specific areas. 
There are plans to reform the Estonian system of postal codes. 
Cooperation will continue with the issue of postage stamps and 
the training of staff. 

</TEXT>

