<H3> <TI>   Election Commission Extends Deadline for Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Election Commission Extends Deadline for Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0205150194 Tallinn BNS in English 1350 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0205150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, 2 May, BNS -- The Central Electoral Committee 
extended the deadline for accepting lists of candidates by 9 May 
in a number of regions. It also decided to convene a meeting of 
election coordinators, Budget Minister Janis Platais and MP's to 
tackle the financial problems of elections. 
  As reported, the Central Electoral Committee requested the 
related institutions to increase the funding for the elections. 
Platais said the claim was ungrounded. 
  Electoral Committee member Dzintars Rasnacs stressed that 
the 
work of regional commissions may be hampered by the lack of 
resources and the financial shortfall may even obstruct the 
organization of local elections. The committee plans to inform 
about the situation Prime Minister Valdis Birkavs if the 
resources are not allotted soon. 

</TEXT>

