BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladas Burbulis] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius 2 May TASS -- Lithuanian President Algirdas 
Brazauskas praised Russian-Latvian agreements reached in Moscow. 
  "The negotiation process with Russia which has caused many 
disputes in Latvia has ended very effectively, namely with the 
signing of very important documents," Brazauskas said in an 
interview with the national radio on Monday. 
  He said that on Tuesday the leaders of the three Baltic 
states -- Latvia, Lithuania and Estonia -- will meet in Riga, 
adding that "we have what to discuss." 
  Brazauskas recalled that during Polish President Lech 
Walesa's recent visit to Lithuania they signed a treaty of 
friendship and cooperation between the two countries. "I think 
it will be interesting for my Latvian and Estonian colleagues to 
hear our opinion about that document. For my part, I would like 
to learn about the results of Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis's 
visit to Moscow and his talks with Russian leaders," he said. 

