<H3> <TI>   Committee Sues Cosmodrome for Environmental Damage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Sues Cosmodrome for Environmental Damage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205210694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1920 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The command of the Russian launch facility of 
Plesetsk has admitted that rocket launching causes damage to 
nature but has deemed the financial claims excessive. The 
Archangel Oblast Environment Protection Committee is suing the 
cosmodrome for 1.2 billion rubles over the detachable stages of 
launch vehicles that have been falling down for many years near 
the coastal village of Koyda carrying remains of fuel. 
  The case was examined by the arbitration court, which agreed 
with the arguments of representatives of the space industry that 
the amount of economic damage suffered by the territory should 
be calculated more thoroughly. It has been decided to have an 
independent inquiry. 

</TEXT>

