<H3> <TI>   Talks With Estonia Produce No Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With Estonia Produce No Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205180794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1530 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The last round of the Russian-Estonian talks ended 
practically without result, according to Reinart, head of the 
Estonian delegation. Russia has taken the date for completing 
troops withdrawal -- 31 August 1994 -- out of the draft 
agreement, but has not proposed any other date for discussion. 
According to Svirin, head of the Russian delegation, in 
discussions on the sea borders during the talks, disagreements 
were revealed concerning the point where they should be linked 
up with the border on land. Estonia insisted on the 1920 
borders, whereas Russia is for setting the border line from the 
place where the present land border comes down to the Baltic Sea. 
  According to INTERFAX, the next round of talks will be held 
in Tallinn tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

