<H3> <TI>   Greek Foreign Minister's Visit to Moscow Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek Foreign Minister's Visit to Moscow Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305111694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1042 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Yuriy Kozlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 3 May -- The official visit of Greek Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias to Russia, which was planned for 3-5 
May, has been postponed to a later date at the request of the 
Russian side. The date of the visit has not yet been 
determined, Grigoriy Karasin, director of the Press and 
Information Department of the Russian Foreign Ministry, told 
ITAR-TASS today. 
  The main reason for the postponement is linked to the 
signing 
of the agreement "Gaza-Jericho -- First" between the PLO and 
Israel, which will take place in Cairo tomorrow and which will 
be attended by Russian Foreign Minister A. Kozyrev, who left for 
the Egyptian capital today. 

</TEXT>

