<H3> <TI>   Olechowski, Kozyrev Hold Meeting in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Olechowski, Kozyrev Hold Meeting in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904193294 Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network in 
Polish 1730 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Relayed by Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish] </F>
  [Text] [Announcer Jaroslaw Gugala] A private meeting 
between Polish and Russian Foreign Ministers Andrzej Olechowski 
and Andrey Kozyrev has taken place in the Polish Embassy in 
Moscow without the presence of journalists. Minister Olechowski 
believes that the eastern policy is one of the most important 
tasks of Polish diplomacy. 
  [Correspondent Witold Laskowski, Television Information 
Agency (TAI), Moscow, identified by caption] The meeting was a 
of a purely private character, but both politicians had time to 
discuss Polish-Russian relations. It is known, among other 
things, that, in June, Poland will be visited by Prime Minister 
Chernomyrdin, and we can expect the visit of Boris Yeltsin 
himself to attend ceremonies commemorating the 50th anniversary 
of the Warsaw Rising on 1 August. 
  Minister Olechowski confirmed Andrey Kozyrev's international 
reputation of, as he put it, a splendid interlocutor. In the 
opinion of the head of our diplomacy, there is a good climate 
for pushing matters ahead in Polish-Russian relations. We agree 
with the Russians regarding the objective of Europe without 
frontiers, the only difference being that we want to achieve 
this by joining NATO, and the Russians see everything 
differently. 

</TEXT>

