<H3> <TI>   200 Organizations Ready To Join Social Accord Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    200 Organizations Ready To Join Social Accord Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205115494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Over 200 Russian public organizations have expressed 
their readiness on 5 May to join the treaty on social accord, 
which was signed 28 April by the country's main political 
forces. This was announced by Sergey Filatov, head of the 
Russian president's administration. The treaty envisions 
rejection of violent actions to achieve political goals and the 
government has undertaken a number of obligations with a view to 
overcoming the socioeconomic crisis. 

</TEXT>

