<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Cooperation Agreement Signed With French Team </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nuclear Cooperation Agreement Signed With French Team </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0205145794 Tallinn BNS in English 1350 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0205145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, 2 May, BNS -- A French-Lithuanian 
agreement on cooperation in the field of nuclear energy was 
signed in Vilnius Friday by Philippe Rouvillois, director 
general of the French Atomic Energy Agency, and Algimantas 
Stasiukynas, Lithuanian energy minister. 
  A delegation of French nuclear energy experts, headed by 
Rouvillois, visited Lithuania last week to discuss safety at the 
Ignalina nuclear power plant. 
  Vytautas Bieliauskas, head of the nuclear energy division of 
the Lithuanian Energy Ministry, said the European Bank for 
Reconstruction and Development allocated 33 million ECU to 
upgrade safety at Ignalina. The visiting French delegation said 
companies in France are ready to take an active part in the 
Lithuanian power plant's modernization. 

</TEXT>

