<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seimas Introduces Proportional System for Local Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seimas Introduces Proportional System for Local Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0205115294 Vilnius ELTA in Lithuanian 1151 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0205115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Seimas [parliament] has decided that the 
self-government elections will be held according to the 
proportional system. Members of local councils will be elected 
for two years, while their current term in office is four years. 
  The election date has not yet been set. According to 
unofficial reports, the elections should take place this fall. 
  One article in the law on elections for local government 
councils, approved by the Seimas, states that representatives to 
election commissions can be nominated only by those parties and 
political organizations, which have received Seimas deputy 
mandates according to party lists. 
  The entire law on elections to local government councils 
will 
be adopted next week. 

</TEXT>

