<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Good Prospects Seen for Japan Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Good Prospects Seen for Japan Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305174194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A briefing has been held at Ukraine's Foreign 
Ministry to sum up the visit to Japan by the ministry's 
delegation led by Mykola Makarevych, first deputy foreign 
minister. The principal aim of the visit was to lay a 
contractual and legal foundation for Ukrainian-Japanese 
bilateral relations. 
  It was emphasized at the briefing that Japan is one of our 
country's most promising partners. The issue of developing 
bilateral cooperation was discussed at Japan's Foreign Ministry 
and International Trade and Industry Ministry. It was decided 
that there should be an exchange of delegations of specialist 
lawyers to work out documents which would become the basis for 
relations to be enhanced. 

</TEXT>

