<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zlenko Receives French Delegation, Signs Air Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zlenko Receives French Delegation, Signs Air Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305115794 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1050 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 3 May [no dateline as received] -- Ukrainian 
Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko has received a French 
delegation in Kiev on an official visit that is headed by Alain 
Lamassoure, minister-delegate of European Affairs. The sides 
expressed the certainty that relations between the two states 
would reach a new level. 
  An agreement on air transport was signed, as well as an 
agreement on the encouragement and mutual protection of 
investments. A news conference is planned by Lamassoure will 
concern, in particular, economic cooperation and stability in 
Europe, problems of power engineering, and safety of nuclear 
power stations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

