<H3> <TI>   `Mideast Connection' in Planned Terrorist Act </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Mideast Connection' in Planned Terrorist Act </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305121794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1104 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Savchenko of CRIME-PRESS-TASS for </F>
UKRINFIRM] 
  [Text] Donetsk, 3 May -- Staff of Ukraine's Security 
Service have carried out in Mariupol a successful operation to 
seize and unmask a group of foreign citizens who planned to 
commit an act of international terrorism in Moscow. 
  It has been established that "it was the direct intention of 
those detained to commit a terrorist act in an embassy located 
in the Russian capital," Colonel Dmitriy Chernousenko, deputy 
head of a department of the Ukrainian Security Service for 
Donetsk Oblast, stated. No specific targets were named, 
  It was pointed out at a news conference in Donetsk, however, 
that the suggestion that the terrorists had a "Mideast 
connection" is not without foundation. The special services of 
interested foreign states have been briefed on the operation in 
Mariupol. 

</TEXT>

