<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Decree on Reducing Cash Circulation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Decree on Reducing Cash Circulation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305163594 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leonid Kravchuk has issued an instruction 
introducing changes and amendments to the directive on measures 
to reduce cash circulation. Under the directive, with the aim 
of normalizing monetary circulation and reducing the rate of 
monetary emission growth on the territory of Ukraine, all mutual 
one-off payments for goods, work, services and securities to the 
value of more than six minimum wages that are effected by 
corporate bodies, regardless of their forms of ownership and 
kinds of activity, and by Ukrainian citizens, foreign citizens, 
and those without citizenship who carry out entrepreneurial 
activity, are to be solely non-cash. Commercial banks are to 
provide cash only on condition that there are appropriate 
grounds, and are to control its use in order to ensure that it 
is used for the declared purpose. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

