<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev on Mideast Peace, Invitation to Mubarak </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev on Mideast Peace, Invitation to Mubarak </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305181794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1737 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special corrwespondent Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
correspondent Georgiy Shelenkov] 
  [Text] Cairo, 3 May -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, who arrived in Cairo today to attend the signing of the 
Palestine-Israel agreement, has handed a personal message from 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin to Egyptian President Husni 
Mubarak. In the message the head of the Russian state confirmed 
his invitation to H. Mubarak to visit Moscow. This visit, 
Kozyrev told journalists, can take place in the forseeable 
future. 
  Answering questions from journalists after meeting H. 
Mubarak 
at the presidential palace "Al-Ittihadia," the head of Russian 
diplomacy noted that at the meeting Russia's preparedness was 
confirmed to assist further steps along this path together with 
the United States, which co-chairs with Russia the Middle East 
peace process, and Egypt. 
  Tomorrow's signing of the Palestine-Israel document, Kozyrev 
said, "will become a good present" for President Mubarak, who is 
celebrating his birthday on Wednesday. 
  The realization of the Palestine-Israel agreement, the 
minister continued, will present the Palestinians with some 
difficult tasks in implementing autonomy. Russia is ready to 
give them all possible assistance in this. 
  Moscow also intends to contribute to progress in the 
Syrian-Israeli direction of the peace process, too. "We will 
make every effort to bring closer the positions of the sides," 
Kozyrev said. "Maybe we are on the threshold of a new peace 
process, that between Syria and Israel." 

</TEXT>

