<H3> <TI>   ROK, Russia To Swap Information on DPRK Nuke Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK, Russia To Swap Information on DPRK Nuke Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405001894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0008 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405001894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 3 (YONHAP) -- South Korean Defense 
Minister Yi Pyong-tae and his Russian counterpart Pavel Grachev 
have agreed to exchange information on Pyongyang's nuclear 
weapons program in a joint effort to check a major threat to 
world peace, sources at the South Korean Embassy here said 
Wednesday. 
  During Yi's meeting with Grachev Saturday, the two ministers 
shared the view that exchanging such information is essential to 
maintain peace in Northeast Asia and on the Korean peninsula, a 
senior official said. 
  The agreement should help Seoul gauge the progress of 
Pyongyang's nuclear arms development program, he noted. 

</TEXT>

